response:
To view detailed reports for a specific network device interface, use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/reports/child-details/NETWORKDEVICE/INTERFACE/{id}

Replace {id} with the specific network device interface ID to fetch in-depth monitoring data for that interface.

To get the summary report for a monitor group by its ID, use the following API endpoint:

GET /api/reports/summary/group/{id}

This endpoint retrieves the summary report for the specified monitor group, summarizing its monitoring data. Replace {id} with the actual monitor group ID.

No, you cannot delete a Mobile app using the configuration profiles. To delete a specific mobile app entry registered for Mobile/Real-Browser-Monitoring app tracking, you must use the endpoint:

DELETE https://www.site24x7.com/app/api/mobilerbm/delete_app/{id}

The configuration profile endpoints are for deleting Agent Configuration profiles, Business Transaction Configuration profiles, or Auto Upgrade Profiles, not mobile apps.

To check monitor dependencies, use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/dependency/{monitor_id}

Replace {monitor_id} with the specific monitored resource's ID to retrieve its dependency map.

To see detailed information about a Cisco ACI Leaf device, you can use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/reports/child-details/CISCOACI/LEAF/{id}

Replace {id} with the specific ID of the Cisco ACI Leaf device you want details for. This will retrieve detailed child device information for that Leaf device.

To fetch the Azure Virtual Machine disk details report by monitor ID, use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/reports/child-details/AZURE-VM/DiskDetails/{id}

Replace {id} with the specific Azure Virtual Machine monitor ID. This will provide detailed disk usage and status reports for the specified Azure VM.

To fetch the full configuration details for a specific monitor, use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/monitors/{monitor_id}

Replace {monitor_id} with the ID of the monitor you want to retrieve.

To view the stack switch child details for a network device, you can use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/reports/child-details/NETWORKDEVICE/STACKSWITCH/{id}

Replace {id} with the specific identifier of the network device you want to query. This request fetches the stack switch child details report within the NCM device category, providing comprehensive monitoring data on the stack switch configuration and status. Note that this endpoint requires a valid API key to be passed as a query parameter named "apikey" for authentication.

To retrieve the SLO policies linked to a specific monitor in Site24x7, you can use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/slo/get_monitor_associated_slo/{id}

Here, replace `{id}` with the monitor's unique identifier. This call fetches all SLO policies associated with that particular monitor, providing details such as SLO name, target, and status. Note that the response also includes a custom field named `slo_priority` which indicates the priority level of each SLO policy linked to the monitor.

To get the child outages report for a specific monitor by its ID, use the following endpoint:

GET /app/api/reports/child/outages/{id}

Replace {id} with the monitor's unique identifier. This request retrieves detailed reports of all child outages associated with the specified monitor, including incident timings and duration. The response typically includes a JSON array of child outage objects, each containing fields like outageStartTime, outageEndTime, and affectedResources. Note that this endpoint requires an API key passed as a query parameter named api_key, with a default timeout of 60 seconds for the request.

To download the file for a specific custom report by its report ID, use the following API endpoint with the HTTP PUT method:

PUT /app/api/reports/custom_reports/download/{id}

Replace {id} with the actual report ID. This request will return the downloadable file for the specified custom report. Note that this endpoint requires the report ID to identify which report file to download. The response will typically include the file content in PDF format by default.

To retrieve the AWS account ID linked to a specific AWS integration reference in Site24x7, use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/aws/account_id/{aws_account_ref}

Replace {aws_account_ref} with the actual AWS integration reference you want to query. This request will return the AWS account ID associated with that integration reference. Note that this endpoint requires an API key with read permissions to AWS integrations and returns data in JSON format with a 200 OK status on success.

To retrieve polling options for a specific monitor type in Site24x7, you can use the following API endpoint:

GET /app/api/poll_options/{monitor_type}

Replace `{monitor_type}` with the specific type of monitor you want polling intervals for. This endpoint returns the available polling interval options for that monitor type, allowing you to understand and configure how frequently the monitor collects data. Note that the response also includes a default_poll_interval parameter, which is set to 5 minutes unless otherwise specified.
